metadata.name: Snow Night Generative #41
metadata.description:
Snow night is a particulate artwork for me.
It mix two discipline, 3D art and Generative art, I wanted to give a try with something that I don't really see a lot on FXHash, mixing a 3D world handly created by me and finished by computer, when I say finished by computer is that the computer pick the color (In Six palettes), the snow size and speed for final render of artwork !

I hope you enjoy it !

Made with BabylonJS.

Hash Features :
Six different palettes : 
- Four that have 22.5% chance of being drop
- Monochrome one that have 10% chance of being drop

Radioactivity feature : 5% chances to drop a rare radioactivity features on my artwork !

Two differents snow size : Big and Little
Two differents snow speed : Fast and Slow

Moon Color : Value in RGB

Snow Night by @Disjonquille
Inspired by Jukimoot !

metadata.name: Lost Twins #47
metadata.description:
Individually, the mints of this token are very simple. Each mint generates half of two cube forms, and each half is assigned random hues (in multiples of 10, from 0 to 360). Collectively as a project, this token challenges the approach of looking for "rarities" in a new way. How the cubes are rendered leaves the possibility for multiple mints to potentially join up on the sides with colors that perfect match each other. Will you find your lost twin?

Made in p5js
Created November 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Lines and reflections, burn. #51
metadata.description:
The repetitions of the lines form the sequence, the refraction of the lines in polarization angles is generated through repetitions of the lines and divisions of the Brewster angles, but the light here is not emitted from a single point of reference, the light and shadow is a result of the accumulation of lines in a point of polar refraction, where the oscillators indicate the object its changes, the repeated triangles are images of the first reflection, those with larger numbers are successive reflections.

Hydra/javascript on hash, highly. Marcelo Moura
